<BaseLayout title="About" description="Professional background and experience of Tim Dennis, Director of the UCLA Library Data Science Center.">
	<h1>About Tim Dennis</h1>

	<section>
		<h2>Professional Overview</h2>
		<p>
			I serve as Director of the UCLA Library Data Science Center, where I lead initiatives in
			research data services, open science, and computational training. With 26 years of experience
			in the UC system, I focus on building capacity for reproducible research and advancing library
			leadership in the digital research landscape.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Current Role & Responsibilities</h2>
		<p>As Director of the UCLA Library Data Science Center, I oversee:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Research data management and open science initiatives</li>
			<li>Computational training programs and workshops</li>
			<li>Grant development and management for major funding initiatives</li>
			<li>Strategic partnerships across the UC system and national networks</li>
			<li>Team leadership and professional development</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Areas of Expertise</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Open Science and Reproducible Research</li>
			<li>Research Data Management and Infrastructure</li>
			<li>Library Leadership and Strategic Planning</li>
			<li>Grant Writing and Project Management</li>
			<li>Computational Training and Education</li>
			<li>Academic Library Innovation</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

